0g";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:600;s:6:"height";i:1000;s:6:"source";s:54:"https://www.wcmanet.org/garage-door-spring-adjustment/";s:6:"domain";s:15:"www.wcmanet.org";}}s:9:"sentences";a:74:{i:0;s:14:"Answer 1 of 3.";i:1;s:49:"1 Check to make sure the opener is getting power.";i:2;s:53:"Simply push the button and see if the light comes on.";i:3;s:94:"If the light does not come on then check the power by plugging a light or fan into the socket.";i:4;s:59:"Maybe it is as simple as a GFI or circuit breaker flipping.";i:5;s:20:"However if you hear.";i:6;s:121:"The chain breaking means there was a lot of force on that chain - ie the door was trying to open and it already was open.";i:7;s:35:"Or close and it was already closed.";i:8;s:73:"Disengage your Door from the chain via the PULL so the door moves freely.";i:9;s:99:"Close the door by hand manually - make sure it is disengaged from the Chain Rail via the pull rope.";i:10;s:59:"My garage door wont move but the motor and chain is moving.";i:11;s:49:"The right sensor is green but the left is yellow.";i:12;s:25:"Ill do all I can to help.";i:13;s:42:"Can you tell me more about whats going on.";i:14;s:66:"When I push the button the chain moves but doesnt engage the door.";i:15;s:84:"Some problems are associated with the actual installation of the garage door opener.";i:16;s:110:"If the rail system is not perfectly level the chain can eventually bind up in the process of working the door.";i:17;s:78:"Also the garage door slides along two door rails on either side of the garage.";i:18;s:70:"Place a level on these and the rail to check to see if they are level.";i:19;s:29:"4 Answers from these members.";i:20;s:51:"Remove the cover and take a look at the drive gear.";i:21;s:52:"It is white nylon and is just in front of the motor.";i:22;s:79:"You will find it stripped and what looks like white sawdust all over the place.";i:23;s:58:"The part number is 41A2817 and it comes with instructions.";i:24;s:118:"The first step is to locate the emergency release and disengage it do it only if the garage door is completely closed.";i:25;s:59:"Detach the opener by pulling the emergency handle downward.";i:26;s:62:"The next step is to attempt to open your garage door manually.";i:27;s:79:"This will determine if the issue is connected to the door itself or the opener.";i:28;s:176:"If the motor inside your garage door opener sounds like it is turning but the belt chain or screw is not moving you may have a broken or defective part inside the motor itself.";i:29;s:97:"If this is the case you will want to call a trained service technician to repair the door opener.";i:30;s:99:"Theres something wrong with the garage door opener thats stopping it from opening the door for you.";i:31;s:90:"In most cases the cause will be a stripped gear or a chain that has come off the sprocket.";i:32;s:70:"If this is the case the motor will run but as the chain isnt where it.";i:33;s:54:"So I just closed the garage with the chain disengaged.";i:34;s:198:"The motor will start and stop in response to button pushes like it is supposed to - normally the first push starts it in one direction the 2nd reverses the direction and the 3rd will stop the motor.";i:35;s:81:"However the chain has completely stopped moving and by extension so has the door.";i:36;s:62:"What could be causing my garage door opener chain to not move.";i:37;s:78:"If it does not lock into position examine both the connector and the receptor.";i:38;s:74:"Check the connector between the chain and the door it may be disconnected.";i:39;s:94:"In this video Ill show you the issue with a garage door opener that makes noise but wont move.";i:40;s:51:"The opener motor is fine but the shaft doesnt turn.";i:41;s:50:"Without any warning the garage door will not open.";i:42;s:92:"You can hear a click like relay is picking up and light comes on so elec connection is fine.";i:43;s:40:"No movement of drive chain and sprocket.";i:44;s:75:"As a result because its not